cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.CL 

This paper deals with recognizing personality traits from short videos using deep neural networks. The use of visual features and audio signals suggests that the paper could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep neural networks suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with natural language processing (NLP) to some extent, which suggests that it could belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with stochastic features, which suggests that it could belong to the statistical learning (cs.SD) sub-category.
